// test/sema/resolution/submodule_port.test — `SUB.port` scoped-name
// fixture (T023 rollover; specs/006-m3-sema/tasks.md Phase 4a).
// Asserts that the head of a multi-part `<inst>.<port>` reference
// resolves to the submodule instance at minimum (Phase 3's ships
// head-only resolution; full multi-part walk lands at Phase 4b T058
// / S20 — at that time the `: BitVector(N)` Type suffix on the
// FieldAccessExpr will become precise).
//
// Per `emit-ast-format.contract.md` Invariants 2 + 3 (ASCII
// separators per Invariant 7).

// RUN: printf 'module m {\n  cpu_t inst;\n  reg q = inst.port;\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK: (ModuleBlock {{.*}}name=m
// CHECK: (SubmoduleDecl {{.*}}templateName=cpu_t
// CHECK: (FieldAccessExpr
